CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 19,1945 page 13 reads: "Poster Contest winners-- Winners in high school competition sponsored by the Pittsburgh Branch of Federal Union, Inc, pose with their entries at Carnegie Museum. Left to right: Joseph Schumacher, junior at Connelly Vocational School; John Wall, senior at Peabody High; Roland Lucas, senior at Peabody High; Roland Lucas, Senior at South Hills High." -- Harris Photo.
TitMainTitle: John Wall holding sign inscribed "The Guiding Light to a Sure Peace, Federal Union," next to cabinet with feathered masks
